  <revision rev="20" vrev="831">
    <srcmd5>cf2297410ecf9f055a441f043b73d565</srcmd5>
    <version>2000.11.03</version>
    <time>1779981848</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- jsc#PED-14844: Remove unnecessary systemd-tmpfile.
- Specfile cleanup
  * Change Source0 URL to the redirect of the previous URL.
  * Convert ISOgrk5.gz to .zip (content unchanged)
    in order to clean up the %prep section.
  * Change URL to something more informative.
  * Drop unneeded sgml-skel BuildRequires.
- Trim whitespace in .changes file.
- Fix jsc#PED-14844 for immutable mode
  * No changes in tarball
  * Use %autosetup
  * Some code cleanup
  * Add systemd-tmpfile
- Use %patch -P N instead of deprecated %patchN.
- Modernise spec file
- change license to some spdx.org form - this a standard from w3.org,
  so it can be distributed pretty much freely
- make patch0 usage consistent
- Add BuildRequires: unzip
- Fix %postun script; reported by Andreas Hanke [# 175611].
- modify setup line in spec file
- converted neededforbuild to BuildRequires
- added option # norootforbuild in specfile
- Use %postun for catalog removal.
- Use sgml-register-catalog to add catalog to /etc/sgml/catalog.
- Add lost ISOgrk5 (bug #4212).
- Mor spec file macros.
- Added_Latin_1 has to point to ISOlat1 (not ISOLat1) and Added_Latin_2
  to ISOlat2 (not ISOLat2).
- General cleanup.
- Use date string as version number.
- Now, it's noarch.
- ran old prepare_spec on spec file to switch to new prepare_spec.
- fixed call of Check at the end of %install section
- Provide a maybe useful link /usr/share/sgml/CATALOG.iso_ent.
- Install CATALOG as /var/lib/sgml/CATALOG.iso_ent.
- Add CATALOG file.
- Provide a link for ISOgrk5.
- Make Makefile.Linux and friends obsolete.
- Don't escape `:' in file names of the %files list.
	* correct %install section.
	* initial package.
</comment>
    <requestid>1355374</requestid>
  </revision>
</revisionlist>
